        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 2 at 7:11PM PDT by NWS Missoula MT</headline>
        <description>At 710 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms 8 miles northeast of Riggins, or 29 miles south of
Grangeville, moving north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph, continuous moderate-to-heavy
rainfall, and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grangeville, Kooskia, Riggins, White Bird, East Kamiah, Clearwater,
Stites, Riggins Hot Spring, Lucile, Glenwood, Woodland, Winona, Slate
Creek, Harpster, and Fenn.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
